@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "What is Frontend?";
}

<div class="container">
    <h1>What is Frontend?</h1>
    <p><strong>Frontend</strong> is everything you see and interact with on a website or app — the buttons, pictures, text, and colors.</p>

    <p>Imagine you are drawing a picture. The drawing is what everyone sees and enjoys. Frontend is like that picture — it shows what the website looks like and lets you click and play with it.</p>

    <p>So, Frontend helps us <strong>show</strong> information and <strong>interact</strong> with the website in a fun and easy way.</p>

    <div class="navigation-buttons">
        <a href="@Url.Action("WhyFrontend", "Frontend")" class="btn btn-primary">Next &raquo;</a>
    </div>
</div>

